    • Method Detail

      • acquireSyncId

        @GET(value="/datastore/sync/{entitySetId}")
java.util.UUID acquireSyncId(@Path(value="entitySetId")
                                                                         java.util.UUID entitySetId)
        Generates a new sync id for an entity set. If the entity set has no current sync id, the new one is set as current.
        Parameters:
        entitySetId - The id of the entity set to generate a new sync id for.
        Returns:
        A new time-uuid generated in data source api.

      • getCurrentSyncId

        @GET(value="/datastore/sync/{entitySetId}/current")
java.util.UUID getCurrentSyncId(@Path(value="entitySetId")
                                                                                    java.util.UUID entitySetId)
        Retrieves the current sync id for the given entity set
        Parameters:
        entitySetId - The id of the entity set to load the current sync id for.
        Returns:
        The current time-uuid for the entity set.

      • setCurrentSyncId

        @POST(value="/datastore/sync/{entitySetId}/{syncId}")
java.lang.Void setCurrentSyncId(@Path(value="entitySetId")
                                                                                      java.util.UUID entitySetId,
                                                                                      @Path(value="syncId")
                                                                                      java.util.UUID syncId)
        Sets the current syncId for the entity set to the specified syncId. By default, reads for the entity set will come from the current syncId, and writes will be written to the current sync, unless otherwise specified.
        Parameters:
        entitySetId - The id of the entity set to set the current sync id for.
        syncId - the sync id that will be set as current

      • getLatestSyncId

        @GET(value="/datastore/sync/{entitySetId}/latest")
java.util.UUID getLatestSyncId(@Path(value="entitySetId")
                                                                                  java.util.UUID entitySetId)
        Retrieves the most recently created sync id for the given entity set
        Parameters:
        entitySetId - The id of the entity set to load the latest sync id for.
        Returns:
        The latest time-uuid for the entity set.
